Package nusri.fyp.demo.roboflow.data.entity

Class KeypointsPrediction

java.lang.Object
nusri.fyp.demo.roboflow.data.entity.KeypointsPrediction
public class KeypointsPrediction extends Object
Prediction details for detected keypoints, including bounding box, confidence, and individual keypoints.
This class is used in tasks where the goal is to detect multiple keypoints in an image, such as human pose estimation or object keypoint detection.

    • trackerId

      private Integer trackerId
      The tracker ID for the detection.
      This value is used for tracking the object over time in video or multi-frame inference tasks.

    • detectionId

      private String detectionId
      The detection ID for the prediction.
      This is a unique identifier for the specific detection, often used for referencing or correlating detections.

    • parentId

      private String parentId
      The parent ID for the prediction.
      This value is used to link the current detection to a higher-level entity (e.g., a human pose being tracked).

    • keypoints

      private List<Keypoint> keypoints
      A list of keypoints detected within the bounding box.
